{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"444f6d8a-4971-472e-a0db-a33bedadf6d0","content":"### 3. Other v4 gotchas to watch for\n\n| Area | Change |\n|---|---|\n| **`[DataRow(null)]`** | Passing `null` as the first arg is now ambiguous; use `new object[] { null }` |\n| **Cleanup timing** | `[ClassCleanup]` defaults to `EndOfClass` instead of `EndOfAssembly` |\n| **`Assert.AreEqual` on doubles** | Tolerance overloads are stricter; implicit conversions may fail |\n| **Parallelism** | Parallel execution is now enabled by default at the **method** level |\n| **`[Timeout]`** | Applies to the test body only; setup/cleanup time no longer counts |\n\nIf you need per-test setup logic that used `TestName`, move it to `[TestInitialize]` where the instance-level `TestContext` is fully populated.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5880d725-a0f8-4087-bb04-ddc5fc528166","outputTokens":215,"requestId":"1BD2:2912D8:BF18B7:D7A667:6A03F1DF"},"id":"bfcd192f-a3ef-4059-a5a3-0fc6274bb44b","timestamp":"2026-05-13T03:37:10.862Z","parentId":"32efade5-a5f1-4fa7-b731-a80286902e2c"}
